modules.description: This module defines configuration settings for exporting telemetry data via HTTP using Cohttp and Lwt. It includes fields for specifying endpoints, headers, batching behavior, and timeouts for traces, metrics, and logs. The `make` function constructs a validated configuration instance, while `pp` formats it for debugging.

This module implements an OpenTelemetry HTTP exporter using Cohttp and Lwt for asynchronous telemetry data transmission. It provides functions to configure and set up a backend with customizable endpoints, headers, timeouts, and batching behavior for traces, metrics, and logs. Concrete use cases include exporting telemetry data to a remote collector over HTTP(S), with support for async execution and resource cleanup.
